<br>
You will be able to sleep again, eventually.  I do have a suggestion though, however, it will depend on if you have more kids and the age gap.<br>
<br>
After my son was a little over a year old, my wife and I would take turns getting up with him on Saturday mornings.  (My job lets me have weekends off)  So, every other week one of us would get to sleep in.  We would do different things.  As he got older, some days we would go downstairs, have breakfast and watch cartoons (suitable ones, of course) or sometimes I would take him to McDonald's for breakfast.  My wife would do the same.  It gave each of us a break as well as each of us getting some one on one quality time with him.<br>
<br>
I know you are a ways from that at this point, but it's just a suggestion for the future.<br>
<br>
God bless you and your family. <p>Christians know that it is not possible to reject or ignore God without demeaning man<br>
